# Sprint Planning Report — Sprint 2

## Sprint Number & Dates

**Sprint:** Sprint 2  
**Start Date:** 27 January 2026  
**End Date:** 10 February 2026  

Sprint duration: 2 weeks.

---

## Sprint Goal

The goal of Sprint 2 is to establish the initial technical foundation of the project.

This includes designing and implementing the relational database, setting up a Dockerized database environment, and integrating the database with the backend web application.  
By the end of the sprint, the system should support basic data operations and provide a working backend connected to the database.

---

## Selected Product Backlog Items

The following product backlog items were selected for Sprint 2:

- Design of the Entity–Relationship Diagram (ERD)
- Implementation of the relational database schema
- Dockerized setup of the database environment
- Backend integration with the database
- Basic CRUD functionality for core entities
- Initial backend testing and code coverage analysis
- Basic project structure setup (backend and frontend folders)

These items were selected to ensure a functional backend and data layer for further development.

---

## Planned Tasks / Breakdown

The planned tasks for Sprint 2 include:

- Create the Entity–Relationship Diagram (ERD)
- Design and implement SQL schema based on the ERD
- Set up MariaDB using Docker Compose
- Create and populate seed data for development and testing
- Integrate the database with the backend application (Python)
- Implement backend API endpoints
- Implement basic CRUD operations
- Add initial unit tests and perform code coverage testing
- Create basic frontend folder structure and initial landing page
- Maintain and update the project repository on GitHub

